The Minister of Information and Culture, Lai Mohammed, and a former governor of Anambra State, Peter Obi, are among the personalities expected to speak at the fourth annual lecture of Freedom Online. According to a statement by its Managing Director/Editor-in-Chief, Gabriel Akinadewo, the event, scheduled to hold at Radisson Blu Hotel, Ikeja, Lagos, on Tuesday, would focus on “ensuring that Nigeria takes its rightful place in the comity of nations”. He said the annual event “brings together captains of industry, media chiefs, politicians and professionals to reflect on national issues and propose an objective course of action”. Akinadewo explained that while Mohammed would serve as the guest speaker, a former Governor of Kaduna State, Senator Ahmed Makarfi, would chair the session. According to him, a former Governor of Ogun State, Otunba Gbenga Daniel, would deliver the keynote address, with Obi as the special guest speaker. Among other guests expected to attend the event are a former deputy national chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party, Chief Olabode George; former Minister of Police Affairs, Capt. Omoniyi Olubolade (retd.); former director-general of the Nigerian Maritime Administration and Safety Agency, Dr Dakuku Peterside; Aare Ona Kakanfo of Yorubaland, Iba Gani Adams; President and Chairman of Governing Council,  Nigerian Institute of Public Relations, Mallam Mukhtar Sirajo; and Prof Akin Onigbinde. The statement added, “Since the first edition of our annual lecture, we have been inspired by the commitment of our guests and Nigerians in the quest for a better country through advocacy. “We believe this time around, the same zeal will be deployed to ensure that Nigeria takes its rightful place in the comity of nations.”